      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in 50:50 weight distribution and power-to-weight efficiency. This specimen features the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine, maintaining perfect compression across all rotor faces. The factory vacuum line 'rat's nest' is pristine, ensuring seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos. Power is routed through a precise five-speed short-throw manual to a Torsen limited-slip differential. The lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension remains tight, providing the telepathic turn-in these chassis are renowned for. This is a preserved, numbers-matching example with zero thermal degradation of the interior plastics or oxidation of the subframe.",
